POSITION SUMMARY 

Performs highly responsible administrative, professional and supervisory oversight to data and analytics across the Authority. Advises COTA leadership and project teams on data capabilities to identify best practices based on evidence and analytical findings.  

Performs duties in alignment with the 2019 2024 COTA Strategic Plan and in support of the organization's vision To Move Every Life Forward. 

POSITION RESPONSIBILITIES 


Directs the Authority-wide mission to instill a culture of evidence and inquiry by applying the use of data in planning, implementation, assessment, and decision making in a collaborative environment across all divisions through presentations, trainings, and other efforts; 


Develops and implements a data and analytics strategy based on the Strategic Plan for Authority-wide projects and initiatives; 


Provides oversight for all data acquisition across the organization and understands sources, purposes, and usage opportunities both internally and externally; 


Oversees the integrity and analysis of data information that shapes the public understanding of the Authority; 


Understands existing reporting and analytics processes and identifies innovative strategies for enhancements;  


Conducts research and remains current with emerging technologies and solutions in support of future data acquisition and management efforts;  


Advises COTA leadership on data capabilities in support of various projects, initiatives, dashboard capabilities and reports;   


Collaborates with COTA leadership to define data requirements for new business initiatives particularly in the areas of BI, analytics, and data warehousing; 


Provides relevant, timely, and accurate data analytics reporting and information to all relevant key stakeholders and COTA leadership; 


Partnering with various COTA divisions including collaboration with Legal and Procurement to ensure data ownership and necessary clauses are included in all contracts and procurements; 


Serves as a liaison with external data providers;  


Provides oversight to advance projects and initiatives; and  


Ability to work across various departments to establish common business definitions and rules on key performance indicators based on the current environment with the ability to build conceptual data models as the organization continues to grow.  


Manages and provides leadership for his/her staff.  Hires, trains, develops, and appraises staff effectively. Ensures the Authority meets its EEO responsibilities by assisting in identifying problem areas, participating in local minority organizations, participating in review of complaints alleging discrimination, and supporting career counseling for employees. Takes corrective action as necessary, on a timely basis, and in accordance with policy; 


Supports leadership in ensuring that the organization is aware of current state and future expectations; 


Analyzing databases to assess accessibility and accuracy and identifying opportunities for new data sources; 


Partner with IT on existing data infrastructure and reporting environment for analysis of key information within COTA 


Serves as a member on committees requiring data or accountability/performance metrics;  


May be required to be available through a mobile device via voice and/or data during and outside of normal working hours, at the manager's discretion, and must respond within a reasonable timeframe; and  


Performs other duties as assigned. 


QUALIFICATIONS 


Bachelor's degree in Operations Research, Statistics or other related data science field and 7 years of experience in managing data for medium-to-large enterprise is required. An equivalent combination of education and experience will be considered.  


Experience working cross-functionally, managing and building analytical teams, and leading projects with multiple stakeholders.  


Advanced degree and/or certification in advanced analytics and/or statistical analysis/methodologies desired. 


KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS & ABILITIES 


Extensive knowledge of business intelligence practices and tools (e.g., Power BI, Tableau, Microstrategy); 


Experience with SQL, R, SAS, Matlab or other type of data analytics technologies; 


Skills in contract management; 


Knowledge of how to build and manage an effective data operation; 


Ability to define problems, research issues and develop logical and practical solutions within the framework of general principles of information technology project management and the policies and procedures of the Authority. 


Experience with technology-driven change management; 


Ability to understand technology concepts at a high level, and communicate with technical people; 


Skills in verbal and written communication; 


Ability to effectively communicate with internal and external resources to resolve potential conflicts and maintain a teamwork atmosphere;  


Skills in effective stakeholder management; 


Skills in human relations; and  


Ability to direct and lead team members and external contractors.


                POSITION SUMMARY: 

Under the direction of a licensed nurse, the Resident Care Attendant delivers efficient and effective nursing care while achieving positive clinical outcomes and resident/family satisfaction. He/she will function within the standards of practice as accorded by his/her Certification. The Resident Care Attendant performs various resident care activities and related non-professional services essential to caring for personal needs and comfort of residents. 

RESPONSIBILITIES/ACCOUNTABILITIES: 


Provides resident care in a manner conducive to safety and comfort. Resident care includes, but is not limited to: 
Assist resident with or performs Activities of Daily Living (ADL); 
Obtains and records Vital Signs and weights per policy; 
Assists residents with ambulation and transfers; 
Positions residents in correct body alignment in and out of bed; 
Applies adaptive equipment as ordered; 
Cares for personal belongings; 
Assists physician and/or licensed nurse with treatments and procedures as needed; 
Makes both occupied and unoccupied beds; 
Accompanies residents when transported outside the center for appointments as requested; 
Ensures residents are ready for scheduled therapy and transports resident to meals and to outside appointments; 
Participates in the Service Plan process and implements care according to Service Plan; 
Performs skin care treatments, as permitted by state regulation and Service Plan; 
Feeds or assists residents with meals and provides additional nourishment and hydration per Service Plan; 
Records resident's ADL Performance; 
Answers call light or bell promptly, delivers messages, cleans areas of spillage or accidents; 
Uses Standard precautions when caring for all residents. Adheres to Contact and/or Droplet Precautions as indicated. 
Participates in the orientation of new nursing assistants/aides; 
Reports changes in resident's condition, resident/family concerns or complaints to charge nurse and/or supervisor; 
Collects and bags soiled linen to be laundered; 
Assists with the orientation of newly hired Resident Care Attendant /Aides; 
Promotes a culture of safety to ensure a healthy practice and living environment; 
Collaborates and coordinates with other departments to provide timely effective care consistent with the individual's needs, choices and preferences; 
Contributes to an environment that is respectful, team-oriented, and responsive to the concerns of staff, residents, and families; 
Participates in quality improvement activities as requested; 
Maintains confidentiality and protects sensitive Protected Health Information (PHI) at all times; 
Stays and works beyond scheduled shift if needed to meet staffing requirements and/or needs of residents; 
Performs other duties as requested. 


